reviewText: I originally purchased this for a friend and I did view this tape since this film is not available on DVD. It's a good time travel story with an excellent cast with good acting by William Devane, Lauren Hutton, and Klaus Kinski.  Very Enjoyable but for me-the movie even though it's good and rare I consider way overpriced simply because it's not easily obtainable. I would like to see this movie released on DVD. Due to other viewers popularity, it would not be money wasted especially at a normal price and a remastering of the film from an original negative film print

reviewText: You can tell this was made for TV.  Yet there are a lot of good made for TV movies.  This movie has all the elements of future present and past.  There are a lot of "what if's" and some old-fashioned gunplay.Dr. Joseph Cole (Klaus Kinski of Nosferatu fame) a bad guy from the future is determined to change the past for his own nefarious purpose, which could of course changes the present.  This is not nice and must be stopped.  Georgia Crawford (Lauren Hutton) plays the pivotal character that must see that the perpetrator does not do the dastardly deed.  She enlists history professor Scott McKenzie (William Devane) to assist with the technology and events of the time.Zorro, the Gay Blade ~ Lauren Hutton

reviewText: An old west enthusiast named Dr. Scott Mckenzie  (William Devane- THE DARK, PAYBACK), picks up an old trunk at an auction. In it are some vintage western pictures. Mckenzie finds an anomaly in a tin-type photo: a modern item that shouldn't be there. Coincidentally, he is a college professor who happens to be teaching his students about time travel. During class, a bright light flashes, and a woman named Georgia Crawford (Lauren Hutton- SOMEONE'S WATCHING ME) appears! She too is a scientist, and she has arrived to help Mckenzie solve the mystery. Meanwhile, flashbacks show a strange man named Dr. Joseph Cole (Klaus Kinski- CRAWLSPACE, ANDROID, VENOM) gunning his way through the west of 1886. How are he and Crawford connected? Why is she so desperate to track him down? TIMESTALKERS is an interesting, somewhat silly sci-fi / fantasy film. It's rather wacky, w/ a TERMINATOR / DOCTOR WHO time-travel thing going on. Kinski gets to have fun being the murdering, scenery-devouring bad guy, complete w/ long coat and big hat. Also, watch for John Ratzenberger before CHEERS and PIXAR made him a legend!...

reviewText: Come on studio, put it on DVD and make scalpers charging $50 to go broke for being so greedy. The movie is a reasonably good time travel story. William Devane, Lauren Hutton, and the rest the cast turn in good performances. The synopsis says the storyline. A man tries to stop a time traveller that is going back to the past to change history. This story has been seen in a couple others, but this is slightly different and the production values are good. I recommend it once it comes out on DVD for a reasonable price. The outrageous prices being asked here for a used VHS is ridiculous.

reviewText: A 20th century old west freak (Devane) finds a 357magnum in an old time tinplate. He makes a study of the possibility of time travel because of it. In comes time traveler (Hutten) to see if he can help her find her fathers crazy partner (Kinski I believe). But the partner is there for a reason and that is what they have to figure out. Together they ( Devane and Hutten ) travel back and forth through time, to make sure history repeats itself correctly. Great story line, although the acting could be better at times, and for the most part an excellent movie. I really enjoyed it! But it's hard to find though. Watch it if you get the chance. I believe you'll enjoy it if you like the idea of time travel!!!

reviewText: I was looking for this movie and was truely dissappointed to see it's not out on DVD.  It must have been a fun entertaining movie or I wouldn't be here now looking for it on Amazon all these years later.  William Devane makes it believable, I always liked how he acted in this movie. I always enjoyed a good time travel movie and this one was a good one, thats all I am saying.  It's been too many years since I last saw it to leave a better review.  But seriously, if it wasnt any good why would I still be trying to find it to add to my movie collection after so many years.  Too many movies take forever to be put on a DVD.  As if its some big deal to do so.  Compared to some of the crap they so readily produce today and slap on a disc, this should be oscar material compared to those lesser movies.  Come on Hollywood, give us a treat and put this on DVD already!
summary: Old Time Favorite travelling through time

reviewText: This is, simply put; One Of THE BEST Time Travel stories I have ever seen in a film.All the classic elements are there; a villain out to change the future by altering the past, the opposition out to prevent this, temporal anachronisms providing clues, etc... The (dare I say it?) time-honored concept of Paradox is present and accounted for, as expected in a time travel tale...But where this lil` made-for-tv movie differentiates itself is in the myriad little details and the style in which they are presented in a novel and entertaining manner...Without delving into Spoiler Territory, a good example is one scene where the villain manages to beat the tight security of a restricted military installation by simply time-travelling back 60 years BEFORE the place existed, walking a hundred feet, and then going forward in Time again to When and Where he wants to be with no hindrance from armed guards and electric fences. ( Yes...You could say that he 'got PAST' Security!:)The plot is overall intelligent with twists and turns that add up to an engaging "mystery in history", with characterisations that are all good, and acting that is straight forward and believable through-out. Action, Adventure, Pathos, Humor and Intelligence are delivered in ample portions as the story unfolds. This film grabs the viewer on many levels, appealing to fans of Sci-Fi, Westerns...or just anyone who wants a good bit of intelligent Human Drama.True, the plot does have a small hole or two, and some contrived aspects (which is the only reason I did not give it a full "5 Stars") and the time travel-related FX are low-budget tv movie level; but the other production values such as Period Reproduction are top-notch and the aforementioned overall intelligence of the story makes up for such trivialities.It`s too bad that this little Gem appears to be forgotten, with no DVD release (a vhs came out over a decade ago, and my Search turned up ONE copy on Amazon...for FIFTY BUCK$!!...I feel SOOO lucky to have a great-looking print of this already in my collection...I just watched it, which prompted this review)...Here`s hoping such a rare intelligent effort does not remain so terribly ignored.

reviewText: This movie, made for TV, is certainly a cut above the typical 50's or 60s B grade sci fi feature.  The story is interesting, moving from an 1800s western town to present day and 600 years into the future, back and forth.  The editing for all this bouncing around in time is smooth and isn't as distracting as it probably sounds.  The plot and mystery elements are above average.  Sets are good.  The acting is (mostly) quite decent.  For what it is, it's definitely worth watching.  There are some weak moments in the acting delivery and the dialogue missed the quality check in a few spots, otherwise it could sit up there with some of the classics that you might want to watch a few more times.
summary: AN OVERALL ENTERTAINING TIME TRAVEL STORY
